CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 13, 1957, pg. A9, reads: "Beautiful Hats - When the Ladies Auxiliary of the Lincoln Alumni Club gave its annual garden party on the lawn of Emmett Davis, Lincoln Ave., three pretty hats caught the attention of the judges and each of the trio wearing the hats received orchids. Left to right: Miss Elizabeth McCombs, Oswana Nickerson and Mrs. Murrell [Murrel] Wynn Jones. Far right is Mrs. Emily Nickins [Nickens], who emceed the short program. Mrs. Marian Holmes is president. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Elizabeth McCombs, Oswana Nickerson, Murrel Wynn Jones, and Emily Nickens wearing hats and corsages at Ladies Auxiliary of Lincoln Alumni Club garden party at home of Emmett Davis, Lincoln Avenue
